-{"id":"asupersync-tpru","title":"[EPIC-INFRA] Deadline Violation Detection","description":"## Overview

Implement proactive deadline violation detection that warns when tasks are approaching their deadline without apparent progress, before actual timeout occurs.

## Strategic Value

**Problem Solved**: Deadlines are reactive - they trigger cancellation after time expires. By then, it may be too late to understand why. Early warning allows intervention and debugging.

**Proactive Monitoring**: Instead of just enforcing deadlines, we can monitor progress and warn when a task is unlikely to complete in time.

**Production Value**: In production, early warning enables graceful degradation, shedding load before cascading failures.

## Design

### Progress Tracking
Tasks report progress via checkpoints. If time is passing without checkpoints, we know the task is stuck or slow.

```rust
impl Cx {
    /// Report progress toward completion.
    /// 
    /// This resets the "no progress" timer. Call this periodically
    /// in long-running operations to indicate the task is alive.
    pub fn checkpoint(&self);

    /// Report progress with a message.
    pub fn checkpoint_with(&self, msg: impl Into<String>);
}
```

### Violation Detection

```rust
pub struct DeadlineMonitor {
    /// Time without checkpoint before warning.
    pub warning_threshold: Duration,

    /// Callback when approaching deadline.
    pub on_warning: Box<dyn Fn(DeadlineWarning) + Send + Sync>,
}

pub struct DeadlineWarning {
    pub region_id: RegionId,
    pub task_id: TaskId,
    pub deadline: Instant,
    pub remaining: Duration,
    pub last_checkpoint: Option<Instant>,
    pub message: String,
}
```

### Integration with Budget

```rust
let budget = Budget::deadline(Duration::from_secs(30))
    .with_warning_at(Duration::from_secs(25))  // Warn at 25s
    .with_checkpoint_interval(Duration::from_secs(5));  // Warn if no checkpoint for 5s
```

### Stuck Task Detection

If a task has a deadline and makes no progress (no checkpoints, no completion) for a threshold, emit warning:

```
[WARN] Task region-5/task-12 appears stuck
       Deadline: 10s remaining
       Last checkpoint: 15s ago at "processing batch 3"
       Consider: Is this task blocked on I/O? Are there deadlocks?
```

## Usage Example

```rust
async fn process_large_batch(cx: &Cx, items: Vec<Item>) -> Result<()> {
    for (i, item) in items.iter().enumerate() {
        process_item(item).await?;

        // Report progress every 100 items
        if i % 100 == 0 {
            cx.checkpoint_with(format!("processed {}/{}", i, items.len()));
        }
    }
    Ok(())
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

1. Cx::checkpoint() API for progress reporting
2. Warning callback when approaching deadline without progress
3. Configurable warning threshold
4. Integration with Budget system
5. Tracing integration for warnings
6. No overhead when monitoring disabled

## Dependencies

- Uses Budget system
- Benefits from tracing (Epic #2)
- Benefits from attribution (Epic #10)

## Priority Rationale

Ranked #12 because while useful for production debugging, it requires additional work from users (calling checkpoint). The basic deadline system works without this enhancement.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"epic","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T18:09:39.130293818Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-23T02:31:50.234842248Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-tpru","depends_on_id":"asupersync-bg4w","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T06:20:44Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"asupersync-tpru","depends_on_id":"asupersync-mqps","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T06:20:44Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"asupersync-tpru","depends_on_id":"asupersync-ou7o","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T06:20:44Z","created_by":"import"}]}
