 {"id":"asupersync-tvy1","title":"[EPIC-INFRA] Runtime Builder Pattern","description":"## Overview

Implement a fluent builder API for runtime configuration, providing discoverability and validation at construction time rather than runtime.

## Strategic Value

**Problem Solved**: Runtime configuration is scattered across multiple types (LabConfig, RuntimeConfig, etc.). Users must know which options exist and how they interact. Builder pattern centralizes this.

**Why Builder Pattern**: 
- Fluent API is discoverable via IDE autocomplete
- Validation happens at build() time, not later
- Optional features have sensible defaults
- Complex configurations are still readable

**Developer Experience**: New users can configure a runtime without reading documentation by following autocomplete suggestions. This significantly lowers the barrier to entry.

## Design

### Builder Types
```rust
// Main entry point
pub struct RuntimeBuilder { /* ... */ }

// Specialized builders for subsystems
pub struct SchedulerBuilder { /* ... */ }
pub struct TimerBuilder { /* ... */ }
pub struct IoBuilder { /* ... */ }
pub struct TracingBuilder { /* ... */ }
```

### Fluent API
```rust
let runtime = RuntimeBuilder::new()
    .scheduler(|s| s
        .worker_threads(4)
        .task_queue_depth(1024)
        .scheduling_policy(Policy::WorkStealing))
    .timers(|t| t
        .resolution(Duration::from_millis(1))
        .max_duration(Duration::from_hours(24)))
    .io(|io| io
        .max_registered_sources(10_000)
        .enable_uring(true))
    .tracing(|tr| tr
        .enable_structured_logs()
        .span_events(true))
    .build()?;
```

### Lab Runtime Builder
```rust
let lab = LabRuntimeBuilder::new()
    .deterministic_rng(seed)
    .virtual_time()
    .scheduling_oracle(oracle)
    .build();
```

## Validation

Builder validates at .build() time:
- Worker threads > 0
- Timer resolution > 0
- Conflicting options detected
- Required capabilities present

```rust
pub enum BuildError {
    InvalidWorkerCount(usize),
    ConflictingOptions { a: &'static str, b: &'static str },
    MissingRequirement(&'static str),
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

1. RuntimeBuilder with fluent API for all configuration
2. LabRuntimeBuilder for deterministic testing
3. Validation at build() time with helpful errors
4. Sensible defaults (works with just .build())
5. Documentation with examples for common configurations
6. Migration guide from old configuration approach

## Dependencies

- Standalone module, no blockers
- Should coordinate with any config loading features

